      { text: `On the third night in their big bed, something funny happened.\n\nBenjamine dropped his stuffed animal, and it rolled right under the bed.\n\n"Uh oh," said Benjamine.\n\nChristopher leaned over the side and looked underneath. It was dark down there. A little dusty. A little shadowy.\n\nBut then he saw something he had never seen before.\n\nA tiny door.` },
      { text: `It was no bigger than a book, with a round golden handle and a keyhole shaped like a star.\n\nAnd then ‚Äî click ‚Äî it opened. All by itself.\n\nOut came a warm breeze that smelled like cookies and grass and rain. And then out hopped a small, round creature no bigger than a tennis ball.\n\nHe was covered in soft blue fur with two big eyes like marbles.\n\n"Oh! Oh! You found me!" he said. "I'm Tumble! I'm a Dream Keeper. I live under your bed."` },
      { text: `"Under this bed is the doorway," said Tumble. "I live on the other side. In the Underneath. Want to see?"\n\nChristopher looked at Benjamine. Benjamine looked at Christopher.\n\n"Together?" said Christopher.\n\n"Together," said Benjamine.\n\nThey held hands, leaned over the side of the bed, and ‚Äî whooooop ‚Äî tumbled softly, gently, through the tiny door.` },
      { text: `The Underneath was not dark at all.\n\nIt was enormous. A great, wide meadow lit by a sky full of floating lanterns ‚Äî orange and purple and gold. Everywhere, little doors stuck up out of the ground like mailboxes.\n\n"Those are the doors to every child's bed in the whole world!" said Tumble. "And under every bed lives a Dream Keeper. I've been waiting three nights! Dream Keepers can only come out when the children are brave. And tonight ‚Äî you were finally brave enough to find me."` },
      { text: `Tumble led them to the edge where a foggy patch swirled ‚Äî grey and cold.\n\n"That's The Fog. If it covers the lanterns, no child gets good dreams. Inside is a golden lantern. If someone brave lights it, the fog goes away. But I'm too small. I need two children. One to hold the other up."\n\nThey walked in together. The fog whispered: What if it's too dark?\n\n"We have each other," said Christopher.\n\nWhat if Mommy and Daddy aren't here?\n\n"They're coming later," said Benjamine. "They always come."` },
      { text: `Christopher reached for the lantern. Too high.\n\n"Benji, climb on my back."\n\nBenjamine reached out and touched it.\n\nIt exploded with light. The fog turned into hundreds of glowing butterflies that scattered through every tiny door, into bedrooms all over the world.` },
      { text: `Back at their door, Tumble said: "Every single night. Right under your bed. Keeping your dreams safe. When your Mommy and Daddy come to bed later, I send them good dreams too. I'm very thorough."\n\nThey floated back up into bed. The blanket tucked itself around them.\n\nUnder the bed ‚Äî the tiniest humming. No louder than a heartbeat.\n\nTumble. Keeping watch. All night long.` }
