      { text: `Benjamine was counting stars when one moved.\n\nIt wasn't a star. A spaceship. Paw prints on the side.\n\nRyder walked down the ramp in a space helmet.\n\n"Suit up, boys. We're going to the moon."\n\nInside the ship: "Christopher ‚Äî co-pilot. Benjamine ‚Äî chief button-pusher."\n\nA whole panel of colorful buttons.\n\n"Can I push one NOW?"\n\n"Not yet," said Ryder, grinning. "But soon."` },
      { text: `"TEN ‚Äî NINE ‚Äî EIGHT ‚Äî SEVEN ‚Äî SIX ‚Äî FIVE ‚Äî FOUR ‚Äî THREE ‚Äî TWO ‚Äî"\n\nRyder looked at Benjamine. "This one's yours, buddy."\n\n"ONE ‚Äî BLAST OFF!"\n\nHe smashed the big red button.\n\nBOOOOOM!\n\nThe sky went from blue to black to a million billion stars.\n\n"This pup's gotta FLY!" screamed Skye.\n\n"Dude ‚Äî we're in SPACE!" yelled Zuma.\n\nOutside ‚Äî Earth. The whole planet.\n\n"That's where we LIVE," whispered Benjamine.` },
      { text: `"Benjamine ‚Äî push the blue button!"\nPushed.\n"The yellow one!"\nPushed.\n"ALL of them!"\n\nBap bap bap bap bap ‚Äî both hands. Pups cheered. Ryder laughed.\n\nThump. On the moon.\n\nEvery step ‚Äî a giant bouncy jump.\n\nChristopher flew twenty feet. "WHOOAA!"\nBenjamine did a slow-motion somersault. "I'M FLYING!"\nChase bounced into Marshall. "I'm good!" said Marshall, upside down.` },
      { text: `Ryder knelt in moon dust and drew with his finger:\n\nC + B\n\n"That'll be there forever. Your names ‚Äî on the moon."\n\nBenjamine traced the B. Smiled so big.` },
      { text: `Ship flew home. Pups fell asleep one by one.\n\n"Let's dive... in... snore."\n"Rubble on the... snuggle..."\n"Chase is... on the..." "Go to sleep, Chase." Out.\n\nBoys floated into bed. Spacesuits became pajamas.\n\nRyder's voice, soft as starlight:\n\n"Goodnight, astronauts. Your names are on the moon. And the moon is watching over you all night long."\n\nChristopher looked out the window. Moon right there. And somewhere on it ‚Äî C + B.\n\nBenjamine was already asleep. Christopher followed him to the stars.` }
