      { text: `"I don't WANT to go to sleep," said Christopher, arms crossed.\n\nBenjamine's lip wobbled. "My tummy feels bad."\n\n"Like butterflies?" asked Rubble.\n\n"Mean butterflies."\n\n"I get those too! Every time it thunders."\n\n"Really?"\n\n"Every single time, dude," said Zuma. "He hides under my hovercraft."\n\n"ZUMA! That was a SECRET!"\n\nBenjamine giggled.` },
      { text: `"My brain won't stop talking," said Christopher.\n\n"What's it saying?" asked Chase.\n\n"What if something happens. What if I can't sleep and I'm the only one awake."\n\n"My brain says that too. Every. Single. Night. These paws uphold the laws ‚Äî but my brain doesn't listen to laws."\n\nRyder said: "Marshall ‚Äî show them Brave Breathing."\n\nMarshall breathed in slow... then blew out like a faraway birthday candle.\n\nChristopher tried. In... out. In... out.\n\nShoulders dropped. "That actually feels good."\n\n"TOLD YOU! I'm fired up about breathing!"` },
      { text: `"Put your hand on your tummy," said Skye. "Breathe in ‚Äî feel it push out. Like a balloon."\n\nBenjamine breathed in. Hand went up.\n\n"Balloon up."\n\nBreathed out. Hand went down.\n\n"Balloon down."\n\n"Balloon up." In.\n"Balloon down." Out.\n\n"The butterflies are nicer now. Just flying gently."\n\n"This pup's gotta fly," said Skye softly. "And so do your butterflies."` },
      { text: `"When your brain won't stop ‚Äî listen for five sounds," said Chase.\n\n"Rubble breathing." One.\n"Wind outside." Two.\n"Marshall's tail tapping." Three. "Sorry," said Marshall.\n"The house clicky sounds." Four.\n"Benjamine breathing. Right next to me."\n\n"Where's your brain now?"\n\n"It... stopped talking."\n\n"You made it listen instead."\n\nBenjamine tried too. Face all scrunched.\n\n"Rubble's tummy." "That's the treats. Rubble on the grumble."\n\n"Skye's wings." "Good ears!"\n\n"Ryder breathing." "I'm right here."\n"Christopher's heart. Bump bump. It's nice."\n\n"Is the quiet scary?"\n\n"No. It's soft."` },
      { text: `"All together now," said Ryder. Everyone breathed in. The room filled with one big shared breath.\n\nAnd out. Like blowing a bubble you don't want to pop.\n\nOne by one the pups fell asleep.\n\n"Rubble on the... snuggle..."\n"I'm good... I'm..."\n\nBenjamine whispered: "Hey Christopher?"\n"Yeah?"\n"Balloon up."\n\nChristopher breathed in.\n\n"Balloon down."\n\nOut.\n\n"Goodnight."\n"Goodnight, Benji."\n\nAnd two brave breathers drifted off ‚Äî slow and easy ‚Äî like bubbles that didn't pop.` }
