      { text: `Christopher was at the pool edge. Not going in. Nope.\n\nBenjamine on his lap. DOUBLE nope.\n\nA tiny blue fish popped out. Shaking. Wobble wobble wobble.\n\n"HELLO! HELP! I'm in WATER and I DON'T LIKE IT!"\n\n"But you're a FISH," said Benjamine.\n\n"I KNOW! My name is Finley and I'm a fish scared of water. PLEASE can I sit up there?"\n\nHe flopped out ‚Äî SPLAT.\n\n"Much better. Dry. I like dry."` },
      { text: `A BIG grumpy fish appeared. One eye bigger than the other.\n\n"FINLEY. Get back in RIGHT NOW."\n\n"That's my grandpa Gus," whispered Finley.\n\n"I've been swimming FORTY-SEVEN YEARS," said Gus.\n\n"You're not very nice," said Benjamine.\n\nGus blinked. "...Fair enough. Sorry."\n\n"Have YOU ever been scared?" said Christopher.\n\nGus went quiet. "...Boats. I'm TERRIFIED of boats."\n\n"SEE?" said Finley. "EVERYONE'S scared of something!"\n\n"Oh, shush," said Gus. But he was smiling.` },
      { text: `"My mum said ‚Äî don't think about the whole pool. Just get to the next rock." Finley pointed at a tile. Super close.\n\n"Have YOU done it?"\n\n"...No. I get scared and flop back out! I'm a MESS!"\n\nFull-body wobble. Little fins shaking.\n\nBenjamine slid off Christopher's lap. Sat next to Finley. Hand on his back.\n\n"I'll go with you. I'm scared too. So we can be scared together."` },
      { text: `Finley slid in. Benjamine put his feet in. Just feet.\n\n"Ready?" "No! But go anyway!"\n\nOne step. Water at his tummy. Touched the tile.\n\n"WE DID IT!" "I'M AT THE ROCK!"\n\n"Was that hard?" "...No?! WE WERE SCARED OF RIGHT THERE!"\n\n"BLEH PATOOEY!" said Finley, making his disgusting pool-water face.\n\n"BLEH PATOOEY!" said everyone.\n\n"BLEH PATOOEY!" said Gus. Everyone stared. "...What? It's fun."` },
      { text: `Daddy wrapped them in towels. In the warm car, eyes closing:\n\n"Finley was really scared."\n"But he did it."\n"Because YOU helped him."\n\n"Next rock."\n"Next rock, Benji."\n\nSomewhere in a pool, a wobbly little fish was telling his grandpa about two brave boys.\n\nAnd Gus listened. Both eyes watery this time.` }
