      { text: `"I don't wanna go swimming," said Christopher.\n"Me NEITHER," said Benjamine.\n\n"DUDES!" Zuma popped out of their BATHTUB. Goggles on.\n\nMarshall ran in ‚Äî slipped ‚Äî BONK. "I'm good!"\n\nChase: "The swimming case."\n\nRubble waddled in with a rubber duck and pool noodles. "I brought snacks too."\n\n"You can't eat snacks in the pool."\n\n"...I brought snacks too," said Rubble sadly.` },
      { text: `"What if I drink the water?" said Christopher. "It tastes YUCKY!"\n\n"I drank it once!" said Marshall. "GLUG GLUG GLUG! And I made THIS face."\n\nTongue out. Eyes crossed. Cheeks puffed.\n\nBenjamine SCREAMED laughing.\n\n"You just go BLEH and spit it out!"\n\n"BLEH!" "BLEH!" "BLEH BLEH BLEH!" said everyone.` },
      { text: `"First time I got in the ocean ‚Äî I cried," said Zuma.\n\n"YOU?! The WATER pup!"\n\n"Ryder put his feet in. I put my paws in. It was warm. Swishy swishy. Then legs. Then tummy. Then one day ‚Äî SPLASH. But it's not a race, dude. It's a pool."\n\n"Benjamine," said Skye. "You cried at swimming?"\n\nLip wobbled. "A LOT."\n\n"First time I flew ‚Äî I cried! Crying means you're doing something brave. You WENT. You were THERE."\n\n"I WAS there! Brave AND crying!"\n\n"The bravest kind!" said Rubble.` },
      { text: `"Your teacher?" said Chase. "She's YOUR Ryder. She's got you."\n\n"Maybe I'll try listening," said Christopher.\n\n"GROUP HUG!" yelled Rubble. Pups piled on.\n\n"Paw Patrol on the SPLASH!" yelled Zuma.\n"That's not the saying," said Chase.\n"It is NOW!"\n\nThe pool didn't seem so scary. Still big. Still new. But they had each other. And a really good BLEH face.` }
